10 (2) The Flag of Remembrance may be flown along with the American flag and the
11 state flag of the Commonwealth of Kentucky each September 11, which is known
12 as Patriot Day under 36 U.S.C. sec. 144, as a remembrance of September 11,
13 2001.
14 (3) The Freedom Flag shall be designed as follows:
15 (a) The inner portion of the flag shall feature a blue background to represent
16 all Americans united together for freedom;
17 (b) The blue background shall have a white star to represent all who lived and
18 died for freedom;
19 (c) Five (5) white bars shall surround the white star to represent the Pentagon
20 and the organized protection of American freedom;
21 (d) The outer portion of the flag shall feature three (3) white stripes, two (2)
22 narrow red stripes, and two (2) broad red stripes;
23 (e) The three (3) white stripes on the outer portion of the flag represent the
24 rescue workers, firefighters, police officers, port authority employees, and
25 others who worked tirelessly during and after the terrorist attacks of
26 September 11, 2001;
27 (f) The two (2) broad red stripes on the outer portion of the flag represent the
